        <h1>Ballroom Legend</h1>
        <p class="intro">
          Monty’s lifelong devotion to dance is the rare discipline he remembers without prompting—precision steps,
          musical instincts, and a joy that keeps him gliding long after the orchestra stops.
        </p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main class="container">
      <section class="cards-grid expanded-grid" aria-label="Ballroom highlights">
        <article class="card" id="dance-memory-01">
          <div class="card-link">
            <h2>Newport Debut</h2>
            <p class="card-meta"><span class="meta-label">ID:</span> DNC-01 <span aria-hidden="true">•</span> <span class="meta-label">Date:</span> June 12, 1969</p>
            <p>
              At his first Preservation Society gala, Monty astonished society elders with a Viennese waltz so exacting that the
              orchestra’s conductor asked for his rehearsal notes.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="card" id="dance-memory-02">
          <div class="card-link">
            <h2>Signature Spin</h2>
            <p class="card-meta"><span class="meta-label">ID:</span> DNC-02 <span aria-hidden="true">•</span> <span class="meta-label">Date:</span> February 4, 1988</p>
            <p>
              During a benefit at the Plaza, Monty improvised a reverse spin-and-dip sequence. Dancers now call it the
              “Montgomery Loop,” and he beams every time he hears it announced.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="card" id="dance-memory-03">
          <div class="card-link">
            <h2>Why He Loves It</h2>
            <p class="card-meta"><span class="meta-label">ID:</span> DNC-03 <span aria-hidden="true">•</span> <span class="meta-label">Date:</span> Present Day</p>
            <p>
              Monty says ballroom reminds him that grace can be rehearsed: “On the floor, every step forgives the last. That’s why
              I keep dancing.” His archive staff logs weekly studio sessions as memory therapy.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
